Cape Town In what is believed to be one of the biggest drug hauls in the country police in Villiersdorp in the Overberg seized 253 boxes of cocaine and arrested three suspects.&quot;The suspects aged 23, 27 and 42 have been charged with possession and dealing in drugs. They are expected to appear in court soon,&quot; police spokesperson FC van Wyk said. &quot;SAPS crime scene and forensic experts are still on the scene. &quot;The drugs are estimated at R500 million and are believed to have been destined for the export market.&quot;Cape Argus